1️⃣ What is Web Scraping?

Web scraping means extracting data from websites automatically using code.

Example uses:

Collect product prices

Gather news headlines

Research data collection

Job listing analysis

Instead of copying manually, Python can fetch and extract data automatically.

2️⃣ Libraries Used for Web Scraping

Most common libraries:

requests → download webpage

BeautifulSoup → extract data from HTML

Install:

pip install requests
pip install beautifulsoup4
3️⃣ Download a Web Page

Example:

import requests

url = "https://example.com"

response = requests.get(url)

print(response.text)

This prints the HTML code of the webpage.

4️⃣ Parsing HTML with BeautifulSoup
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests

url = "https://example.com"

response = requests.get(url)

soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, "html.parser")

print(soup.title.text)

Output:

Example Domain
5️⃣ Extract All Links
for link in soup.find_all("a"):
    print(link.get("href"))

This prints all links on the page.

6️⃣ Extract Specific Data

Example: Get all headings

for heading in soup.find_all("h1"):
    print(heading.text)
